## Scoring Rubric (Quick Reference)

| Score | Meaning | Criteria |
|-------|---------|----------|
| 0 | Absent | Nothing detected for this tier |
| 1-3 | Minimal | Some tooling exists but incomplete or misconfigured |
| 4-6 | Moderate | Core tooling in place, gaps in coverage or speed |
| 7-8 | Strong | Comprehensive tooling, fast feedback, few gaps |
| 9-10 | Exemplary | Best-in-class, optimised for speed and reliability |

See `references/tiered-test-framework.md` for detailed per-tier scoring criteria.

